"title": "7933: Lord's Supper",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7933",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The commemoration and remembrance of Jesus Christ's last supper, and all the benefits that result to believers. Other terms have been used subsequently by Christians, including “Communion” and “Eucharist”.</p>\n<h2>Terms for the Lord's Supper in the NT</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a> <em>“breaking of bread” could mean both eating together and also celebrating the Lord's Supper</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16\">1CO 10:16</a> <em>The Greek word “koinonia”, here translated “participation”, is traditionally translated “communion”: hence the term “Holy Communion”</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:20\">1CO 11:20</a> <em>the Lord's Supper</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:24\">1CO 11:24</a> <em>Underlying “had given thanks” is the Greek “eucharisteo”, from which comes the term “Eucharist”.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's institution of the Lord's Supper</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:23–11:25</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:26–26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:22–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:17-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:17–22:20</a></p>\n<h2>Celebrating the Lord's Supper in the NT</h2>\n<h3>As part of an ordinary meal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:21\">1CO 11:21</a></strong> <em>The church was not necessarily wrong to include the sacrament in an ordinary meal; this should have been conducted in a charitable way.</em></p>\n<h3>On the Lord's day</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:7\">ACT 20:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:26\">JHN 20:26</a></p>\n<h3>The fourfold formula for breaking bread: taking, giving thanks, breaking, giving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26\">MAT 26:26</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22\">MRK 14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19\">LUK 22:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:30\">LUK 24:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:11\">JHN 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:24\">1CO 11:24</a></p>\n<h3>The sharing of the cup</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:25</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:27-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:27–26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:23-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:23–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a></p>\n<h2>Themes connected with the Lord's Supper</h2>\n<h3>The Passover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7-1Cor5:8\">1CO 5:7–5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:50\">JHN 11:50</a> <em>Caiaphas' words may have an unintended Passover significance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1\">JHN 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:14\">JHN 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:33\">JHN 19:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:36\">JHN 19:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:46\">EXO 12:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:12\">NUM 9:12</a></p>\n<h3>The new covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:25</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:27-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:27–26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:23-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:23–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a> <em>The reference to the (new) covenant implies a personal relationship with God and sins forgiven.</em></p>\n<h3>Remembrance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:24\">1CO 11:24</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19\">LUK 22:19</a></p>\n<h3>Thanksgiving, fellowship and unity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16\">1CO 10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:27\">MAT 26:26–26:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:23\">MRK 14:22–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19\">LUK 22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:20-1Cor11:21\">1CO 11:20–11:21</a></p>\n<h3>The Lord's return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:26\">1CO 11:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:29\">MAT 26:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:25\">MRK 14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:16\">LUK 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:22\">1CO 16:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:20\">REV 22:20</a></p>\n<h3>Separation from sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:21\">1CO 10:21</a></strong> <em>Paul is referring to feasts in heathen temples.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:27-1Cor11:32\">1CO 11:27–11:32</a></p>\n<h3>A foretaste of heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:29\">MAT 26:29</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:25\">MRK 14:25</a></p>",
